# PowerShell Execution

## Overview
After gaining access, I simulated typical post-compromise behavior by launching PowerShell and executing a simple encoded command.

## Attack Execution

powershell
powershell -enc ZQBjAGgAbwAgACIASABhAGMAawBlAGQAIgA=

## Detection in Wazuh
Relevant logs:
- Event ID 4688 – Process creation

Filtering example:
process.name: "powershell.exe"

## Analysis
PowerShell itself is not malicious, but:
- it is commonly abused
- encoded commands are a red flag

This is often where real attacks start to become visible.

## MITRE ATT&CK
T1059 – Command and Scripting Interpreter

## Takeaway
Process monitoring is essential. Without it, this stage would be invisible.
